properties.WarningTitle: AVOID SMOKE (HAZARD REDUCTION BURN) - Bribie Island, Donnybrook, Meldale and Caboolture - fire as at  4:50pm Monday, 31 March 2025
properties.WarningText:
AVOID SMOKE (HAZARD REDUCTION BURN) - Bribie Island, Donnybrook, Meldale and Caboolture - fire as at  4:50pm Monday, 31 March 2025 

 

Warning level: ADVICE

 


Warning area: Bribie Island, Donnybrook, Meldale, Caboolture and surrounding areas


 

Smoke is currently affecting Bribie Island, Donnybrook, Meldale, Caboolture and surrounding areas. This is from a HQ Plantations hazard reduction burn in the Bribie Island State Forest. This fire is under control.




 

What you should do:

- Stay inside and close windows and doors.

- Keep respiratory medication close by.

- Avoid driving through smoke if you can.

- Watch out for firefighters working in the area.

- Do not fly drones around the fire. Drones affect air operations.



 

Impacts:

- Smoke can make it hard for some people to breathe.

- Smoke can make it hard to see when you are driving.

- No properties are at risk



 

Further Information:

- For all warnings, visit the QFD Current Bushfires and Warnings website.

- Follow QFD on Facebook and X.com.

- For road closures, visit the QLD Traffic website or call 13 19 40.

- Visit the Department of Environment and Science website for live air quality data.

- Find out how to get ready for a bushfire on the QFD website under Prepare - Bushfire.



 

Updates will be issued if needed.

 

This warning is from the Queensland Fire Department on behalf of HQ Plantations.

Residents should close their doors and windows and keep medication close by if suffering from a respiratory condition. Motorists should use caution and drive to conditions.
